## Adversarially Robust Persistence Diagrams

::: {.center}
<iframe src="https://sidvishwanath.com/persistence-diagram/index-cols.html" width="100%" height="540px" style="border:none;"></iframe>
:::

::: {.r-stack .center width="80%"}

::: {.content-box-solid-lightorange}
Given a collection of $n$ points $X \in \R^{n \times p}$,+br $\dgm(X)$ encodes multiscale geometric & topological information underlying $X$
:::

::: {.content-box-solid-lightorange .fragment fragment-index=2}
Persistence diagrams are **stable** in the Hausdorff metric, i.e.,+br
small perturbations to $X$ lead to small changes in $\dgm(X)$ (@chazal2016structure)
:::

::: {.content-box-solid-lightorange .fragment fragment-index=3}
But, even a few outliers in $X$ can drastically change $\dgm(X)$, i.e.,+br **Stability $\neq$ Robustness**
:::

::: {.content-box-solid-lightorange .fragment fragment-index=4}
Our work develops a framework for constructing **adversarially robust** persistence diagrams, $\tilde{\dgm}(X)$. +br Our method is computationally efficient and free of tuning parameters. [@vishwanath2022robust; @vishwanath2020robust]
:::

:::


## Adversarially Robust Persistence Diagrams {visibility="uncounted"}

::: {.small}
::: {.footnotesize .center}
$\text{For $m < \frac{n}{2}$,} \quad \text{suppose }  X_{n \times p} = \begin{bmatrix} X^*_{(n-m) \times p} \\ Y_{m \times p} \end{bmatrix}$
:::
where $Y$ are **arbitrary outliers** and $X^*$ are drawn from some distribution $\pr$ with $\supp(\pr) = \mathbb{X}$
:::


::: {.content-box-dblue .small}
**Theorem [@vishwanath2022robust minimax optimality].** &nbsp;&nbsp; For $X \in \Rnp$ in the adversarial setting, let

* $\color{green}{\tilde{\dgm}}(X)$ be the [MoM Dist persistence diagram]{.green}, and 
* $\color{brown}{\hat{\mathsf{d}}}(X)$ _any persistence diagram estimator_,

::: {.center .small}
$$
\begin{aligned}
\left( \frac{m}{n/2-m} \right)^{1/p} &\lesssim \color{brown}{\inf_{\widehat{\mathsf{d}}}} \ \sup_{\pr}\sup_{Y \in \Rnp}\E\bigg( \text{error}\Big( \color{brown}{\widehat{\mathsf{d}}}(X), \dgm(\mathbb{X}) \Big) \bigg)\\[0.5em]
&\quad\quad\quad\quad\quad\quad\lesssim \sup_{\pr}\sup_{Y \in \Rnp}\E\bigg( \text{error}\Big( \color{green}{\tilde{\dgm}}(X), \dgm(\mathbb{X}) \Big) \bigg) \lesssim \left( \frac{m\log{n}}{n/2-m} \right)^{1/p}
\end{aligned}
$$
:::
:::


